{
  "id": "019ce5eb-0930-7f11-9d97-34349917316b",
  "content": "# Docs Workflow Product Design — Key Decisions (2026-03-13)\n\n## D1: Multi-Repo Doc Ownership Model\nEach repo owns its product docs. Workspace has its own docs for cross-cutting decisions. Corvia tracks ALL sources as the unified aggregation layer. Repos are self-contained — a contributor opening just the repo sees everything they need.\n\n## D2: Approach B (Full Loop) Selected\nEnd-to-end write→store→dashboard read loop. Includes: metadata extensions, repo-aware corvia_write, git-triggered re-indexing, dashboard knowledge browser with faceted search, corvia docs check (Aggregator health), and hook enforcement generator.\n\n## D3: Dashboard as Primary Human Read Interface\nHumans don't browse .corvia/ JSON or 30+ RFC files. The corvia dashboard is the detailed read interface. Repos keep only curated overview docs (README, ARCHITECTURE). Everything else is accessed via the dashboard.\n\n## D4: Interactive Graphed Document Reader\nThe dashboard's main view becomes an interactive graphed document reader — replacing the current graph entry view. Knowledge entries rendered as readable documents with visible graph connections. Click to navigate related entries (graph expansion). This IS the navigation model.\n\n## D5: Repo-Aware corvia_write\ncorvia_write gets source_origin metadata (repo:corvia, workspace, memory) and content_role (design, plan, code, memory, finding). Entries are tagged with which repo they belong to.\n\n## D6: Git-Triggered Re-Indexing\nHuman edits docs → git commit → corvia detects changes → incremental re-index. Post-commit hook triggers the update. Markdown files in repos are source of truth for curated docs.\n\n## D7: Hook-Based Enforcement\nPreToolUse hooks on Write|Edit intercept doc writes to wrong locations. corvia workspace init --hooks generates the hook config from corvia.toml workspace rules. Defense in depth: hooks (hard block) + CLAUDE.md (soft guidance) + Aggregator periodic checks.\n\n## D8: Claude Memory Relocated to Workspace\nautoMemoryDirectory setting redirects Claude memory to .memory/ in the workspace. Git-tracked, periodically cleaned. Corvia ingests it alongside other sources.\n\n## D9: Superpowers Path Override via CLAUDE.md\nCLAUDE.md instructions override superpowers default save paths. Product-specific designs → relevant repo's docs/. Workspace decisions → docs/decisions/. Instruction priority: CLAUDE.md > superpowers defaults.\n\n## D10: Aggregator as Maintenance Layer\ncorvia docs check runs periodically. Uses Reasoner to detect: misplaced docs (wrong location), stale docs (semantic drift from code), duplicates (high similarity across sources), missing coverage (semantic gaps). Surfaced in dashboard findings view.",
  "source_version": "docs-workflow-brainstorm-2026-03-13",
